HEADWORD: Lancasterian
<hw>Lan`cas*te"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. a.</pos> <def>Of or
pertaining to the monitorial system of instruction followed by
<person>Joseph <etsep>Lancaster</etsep></person>, of England, in which
advanced pupils in a school teach pupils below them.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lancastrian</ent>⟦br⟧
